# Folder Structure & Styling

## Top-level layout

- **`routes/`** — Route definitions and route-level components (e.g. root layout, index).
- **`features/`** — Feature-based modules. Each feature (and sub-features) lives here.
- **`utils/`** — Shared utilities; same level as `features/`.
- **`infra/`** — Shared integrations (not `lib`): clients (TanStack, Stripe, HTTP) and **services** (adapters that wrap those clients, e.g. `stripe.service.ts`).
- **`errors/`** — Custom error classes (e.g. `errors.ts` or `errors/errors.ts`). Used by services and caught by the global error boundary.
- **`theme/`** — `theme.ts` plus `theme/components/` for shared UI components.

## Feature structure

Each feature (and sub-feature) uses this layout:

```
features/
  auth/
    components/   # Feature-specific components
    hooks/       # Feature-specific hooks
    page/        # The actual page(s)
    service/     # Feature-specific service/API
  dashboard/
    components/
    hooks/
    page/
    service/
    reports/     # Sub-feature with same structure
      components/
      hooks/
      page/
      service/
```

- **`components/`** — Components used only in this feature.
- **`hooks/`** — Hooks used only in this feature.
- **`page/`** — Page component(s) for the feature.
- **`service/`** — API or business logic for the feature.

## Infra structure

`infra/` holds **clients** (SDKs, HTTP instance) and **services** (adapters that use those clients, shared across features).

```
infra/
  http.client.ts       # Axios instance, auth, headers
  tanstack.client.ts  # Query client config
  stripe.client.ts    # Stripe SDK instance
  stripe.service.ts   # Adapter: wraps stripe.client, used by features
```

- **`.client.ts`** — Raw client/SDK setup (Stripe, Axios, TanStack Query, etc.).
- **`.service.ts`** — Adapter or shared service that uses a client; e.g. `stripe.service.ts` wraps `stripe.client.ts` and exposes methods used by multiple features.

## Theme & shared UI

- **`theme/theme.ts`** — Theme config (e.g. Mantine or custom).
- **`theme/components/`** — Shared UI (Button, Card, etc.). Each component has a co-located CSS file.

## Types & validation

- **Feature types:** Put TypeScript interfaces and Zod schemas for a feature in **`<feature-name>.types.ts`** inside that feature folder (e.g. `features/auth/auth.types.ts`, `features/banking/banking.types.ts`). Use Zod for validation; inferred types and interfaces can live in the same file.
- **Global types:** Put app-wide types, namespace declarations, and shared type definitions in a single **`types.ts`** (or `global.types.ts`) at the same level as `features/` (e.g. `src/types.ts`). Use this for things like `declare global`, module augmentation, and types used across multiple features.

```text
features/banking/banking.types.ts   # Account, Transaction, accountSchema, etc.
src/types.ts                       # Global types, namespaces, shared enums
```

## File naming: `<name>.<use>.ts`

Use the pattern **`<name>.<use>.ts`** (or `.tsx` where applicable) so the file’s role is clear from its name.

| Location | Use suffix | Example |
|----------|------------|--------|
| `utils/` | `.utils` | `date.utils.ts`, `format.utils.ts` |
| `features/<feature>/service/` | `.service` | `banking.service.ts`, `auth.service.ts` |
| `infra/` | `.client`, `.service` | `tanstack.client.ts`, `stripe.client.ts`, `stripe.service.ts` |
| `features/<feature>/` | `.types` | `auth.types.ts`, `banking.types.ts` |

- **Utils:** `utils/date.utils.ts`, `utils/format.utils.ts`
- **Feature types (interfaces + Zod):** `features/auth/auth.types.ts`, `features/banking/banking.types.ts`
- **Global types:** `types.ts` or `global.types.ts` at src root — namespaces, `declare global`, shared types
- **Feature services:** `features/banking/service/banking.service.ts`
- **Infra clients:** `infra/tanstack.client.ts`, `infra/stripe.client.ts`, `infra/http.client.ts`
- **Infra services (adapters):** `infra/stripe.service.ts` — wraps a client, shared across features
- **Errors:** `errors/errors.ts` — custom error classes (e.g. `NotFoundError`, `ValidationError`)

Use the same idea for other types (e.g. `something.hook.ts`, `something.page.tsx`) where it helps. Components stay as `Name.tsx` with co-located `Name.css`.

## Styling rules

- **No inline styles.** Use CSS (or CSS modules) only.
- **One CSS file per component.** For every `ComponentName.tsx` there is a `ComponentName.css` (or `ComponentName.module.css`) next to it or in an agreed location.

```text
# ✅ GOOD
theme/components/Button.tsx
theme/components/Button.css

features/auth/components/LoginForm.tsx
features/auth/components/LoginForm.css

# ❌ BAD
<button style={{ padding: 8, color: 'blue' }}>Click</button>
```
